cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.IR 

The paper deals with image recognition and uses Convolutional Neural Networks (ConvNet) and Recurrent Neural Networks (RNN) for feature extraction and sequencing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses end-to-end training of the entire model, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the use of neural networks for recognition suggests that it may belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper deals with recognition of license plates, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
